Description: Body fragment of a closed vessel; metallic black glaze, horizontal white band. Hard, orange clay, between Munsell 2.5YR 6/6 and Munsell 2.5YR 5/6 (light red-red); little mica, small white and black inclusions.
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (C), chamber 19 A, bench on west side
Curator's comments: Findspot number '19 A W' scratched by Petrie
Bibliographic references: Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 327)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.208)
Acquisition notes: Found unregistered in the Department in 2010, in a box with other sherds from Tell Dafana.
